name: Hydrogen
description: Hydrogen was produced in the Big Bang and is the most abundant element in the universe.

name: Helium
description: Helium was also produced in the Big Bang and is the second most abundant element in the universe.

name: Lithium
description: Lithium was produced in small quantities during the Big Bang nucleosynthesis.

name: Beryllium
description: Beryllium is produced by cosmic ray spallation in space.

name: Boron
description: Boron is produced by cosmic ray spallation of heavier elements.

name: Carbon
description: Carbon is produced in dying low-mass stars through the triple-alpha process.

name: Nitrogen
description: Nitrogen is produced through the CNO cycle in stars.

name: Oxygen
description: Oxygen is produced in massive stars and is the third most abundant element in the universe.

name: Fluorine
description: Fluorine is produced in asymptotic giant branch stars.

name: Neon
description: Neon is produced through carbon burning in massive stars.

name: Sodium
description: Sodium is produced through carbon burning in massive stars.

name: Magnesium
description: Magnesium is produced in massive stars through silicon burning.

name: Aluminum
description: Aluminum is produced in massive stars through silicon burning.

name: Silicon
description: Silicon is produced in massive stars through oxygen burning.

name: Phosphorus
description: Phosphorus is produced in massive stars through silicon burning.

name: Sulfur
description: Sulfur is produced in massive stars through oxygen burning.

name: Chlorine
description: Chlorine is produced in massive stars through oxygen burning.

name: Argon
description: Argon is produced in massive stars through oxygen burning.

name: Potassium
description: Potassium is produced in massive stars through silicon burning.

name: Calcium
description: Calcium is produced in massive stars through silicon burning.

name: Scandium
description: Scandium is produced in supernovae through the alpha process.

name: Titanium
description: Titanium is produced in supernovae through silicon burning and alpha process.

name: Vanadium
description: Vanadium is produced in supernovae through explosive nucleosynthesis.

name: Chromium
description: Chromium is produced in supernovae through silicon burning.

name: Manganese
description: Manganese is produced in supernovae through silicon burning.

name: Iron
description: Iron is primarily produced in supernovae through silicon burning. It is the most stable element and represents the endpoint of stellar nucleosynthesis.

name: Cobalt
description: Cobalt is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Nickel
description: Nickel is produced in supernovae through silicon burning.

name: Copper
description: Copper is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Zinc
description: Zinc is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Gallium
description: Gallium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Germanium
description: Germanium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Arsenic
description: Arsenic is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Selenium
description: Selenium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Bromine
description: Bromine is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Krypton
description: Krypton is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Rubidium
description: Rubidium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Strontium
description: Strontium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Yttrium
description: Yttrium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Zirconium
description: Zirconium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Silver
description: Silver is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Lanthanum
description: Lanthanum is produced in supernovae through the r-process and s-process.

name: Cerium
description: Cerium is produced in supernovae through the r-process and s-process.

name: Praseodymium
description: Praseodymium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Neodymium
description: Neodymium is produced in supernovae through the r-process.

name: Gold
description: Gold is produced in supernovae through the r-process and neutron star mergers.

name: Platinum
description: Platinum is produced in supernovae and neutron star mergers through the r-process.
